  *For this song, Jimmy's uses a six-string acoustic guitar tuned*  
  *to an open C chord. For those beginners, here is the tuning:*  
   *e| Remains the same*  
   *b| Up 1/2 step to C          X = Percussive sound*  
   *g| Remains the same              with no pitch*  
   *d| Up 1 whole step to C*  
   *a| Up 1 1/2 steps to G*  
   *E| Remains the same*  
  *The second time playing RYTHYM FIGURE 1 is usually when Robert sings the*  
  *chorus, however, in the intro he does not.*  
  *Before playing RYTHYM FIGURE 2, you should listen to the actual song.*  
  *Between the open playing and the few notes with numbers is where the lyrics*  
  *will be inserted in. Also, you should be aware that RYTHYM FIGURE 2 is an*  
  *exact mirror of the string section of the song.*  
  
